Problem: Need to submit a password using SSL/TLS encryption.

Process:
1 - I tried doing nc localhost 30001 to submit the password, however I recieved nothing in response.
2 - I then tried doing openssl localhost 30001, but it returned the error that localhost was an invalid command.
3 - I attempted doing openssl nc localhost 30001, however it too said nc was an invalid command.
4 - I used man openssl and found the s_client command which establishes a network session.

Solution:
I used openssl s_client -connect localhost:30001 and then inputed the password of the current level to get the next password for bandit level 16.
